When examining the market segmentation based on form, the distinction between liquid and powdered milk minerals becomes apparent. Liquid milk minerals are commonly utilized in beverages and dairy products, while powdered milk minerals find application in infant formula, dietary supplements, and functional foods due to their convenience and extended shelf life. The popularity of powdered milk minerals among consumers is attributed to their ease of use and storage, making them a preferred choice for both manufacturers and consumers seeking nutritional fortification in their products.

The application segment of the milk minerals market further emphasizes the diverse uses of these minerals in functional foods, dietary supplements, infant formula, dairy products, and other consumer goods. The incorporation of milk minerals in a wide array of products not only enhances their nutritional content but also drives the overall market growth. The growing demand for fortified foods and beverages, driven by an increasing focus on health and wellness among consumers, is a key factor propelling the market expansion for milk minerals.

